11.2 Wrapper Classes

                               Object
                            ↙     ⬇   ↘
                          ↙   Boolean  Character
                       Number
                         ⬇
        ⬇️     ⬇️     ⬇️     ⬇️    ⬇️     ⬇️
       Byte  Short Integer Long  Float Double


1. Provide a way to use primitive data types (int, char, boolean, etc.) as projects.
2. Automatic conversion between the primitive types and their corresponding wrapper classes.
3. Once created, the value of a wrapper object cannot be changed.
4. Utility Methods: Each wrapper class provides useful methods, like compareTo, valueOf,
                    and parseX (e.g., parseInt for Integer).
5. Required for storing primitives in clg.collection objects like ArrayList, HashMap, etc
6. Allows assignment of null to primitive values when needed.
